Description.LocalizedString: Long, restless nights with a guilty conscience. No time to style the hair.
She embraced her curls and tucked her hair into a bun that displayed a more mature look, like she had aged in a matter of days.
Loosely permed hair, dyed strawberry blond. Feeling like a trend-setter!
Denim and boots for rugged, outdoor living.

She guided Dustin as they danced, her plaid skirt swaying softly to the music. Catching a death stare from the mean girl who had rejected Dustin, Nancy smiled. She told Dustin that in a few years, he’d drive all the girls nuts. He grinned.
Tailored pants for when you’re in the office pitching your story.
Warm layers to track down her friend deep into the woods.
The parents of her "missing" friend were still in the dark. Visiting them added a fresh dollop of guilt on Nancy's full plate.
She spotted him, her little brother’s friend. He looked as sad as she felt, despite being dressed to the nines. She asked him to dance.
A no-nonsense cut for a strong, professional journalist who gets the story despite the odds.
A natural style that looks great as is.
A light pink top with a subtle star-like pattern adorning it.
A striped skirt paired with knee high socks.
A shorter, more mature hairstyle that displays the grit she took on to defend those she loves.
Traveling with only the bare essentials, Nancy piles on thick woolen layers to keep warm no matter the weather or destination.
A sturdy pair of wide jeans that allow for full range of motion.
